Fancy getting on the parking spot property ladder? Well, have we got the opportunity for you. For just £85,000, you could get your hands on a London parking space – you lucky thing. Sandwiched between two walls, the space is just two metres wide by five-and-a-half-metres long. With the average UK car measuring in at 1.82 metres wide, it’ll certainly be a tight squeeze. Prospective buyers will no doubt be wondering how on earth they’ll be able to actually get out of the car once it’s parked. Anyone for squeezing through the hatchback? This golden property opportunity is located in a garage in Rutland Gate in Knightsbridge, just 250 metres from Harrods. It’s being sold by estate agents Nicolas van Patrick and advertised on Rightmove with a listing that reads: ‘A single allocated parking space with in a small garage which is sandwiched between Rutland Gate and Ennismore Mews. ‘The space is approximately two metres wide by 5.5 metres long, with good height. ‘With two automated gates operated by fobs, and CCTV the garage is considered to be very secure. ‘It also benefits from access to water.’ Property hunters have been stunned by the offering, with one commenting: ‘Can you actually get out of that car when parked? Sunroof exit only.’ Another said: ‘How do you reverse into that space without dorking your wing mirrors? And how can you reverse without them?’ Donna Ball, of Bolton, Greater Manchester, said: ‘Having great fun coming back from London looking at house parking prices on Rightmove. How about £85k for this parking spot? ‘North forever.’ Do you have a story to share? Get in touch by emailing MetroLifestyleTeam@Metro.co.uk MORE : Tiny house specialist designs 2.5 square-metre ‘hotel’ for Berlin’s homeless MORE : Pensioner fined £100 after parking for just 85 seconds to pop into One Stop MORE : Desperate drivers use brick filled shopping trolleys to reserve parking spaces